# React components

- Keep components focused on one responsibility.
- Prefer composition over large configurable components with too many props.
- Type all component props explicitly.
- Use semantic HTML first: `section`, `header`, `main`, `footer`, `nav`, `article`, `form`, `button`.
- Use accessible buttons and links correctly: buttons trigger actions, links navigate.
- Avoid unnecessary `useEffect`. Derive values directly when possible.
- Avoid duplicated markup. Extract small reusable components when repetition becomes noisy.
- Keep section components easy to reorder or remove because the client may change the landing structure.
- Do not hard-code contact details, certification names, client references, or legal data inside UI components. Read them from centralized content/config.
